The paper deals with the interpretation of human activity in videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of large-scale commonsense knowledge bases and the inference engine based on energy minimization suggest that the paper may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the fact that the paper uses publicly available datasets of videos suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
